11 Notable alumni of

Jan Dlugosz University of Czestochowa

Updated: February 29, 2024

EduRank

The Jan Dlugosz University of Czestochowa is 2354th in the world, 747th in Europe, and 51st in Poland by aggregated alumni prominence. Below is the list of 11 notable alumni from the Jan Dlugosz University of Czestochowa sorted by their wiki pages popularity. The directory includes famous graduates and former students along with research and academic staff.

Jakub Błaszczykowski

Born in

Poland

Years

1985-.. (age 39)

Occupations

association football player

Biography

Jakub "Kuba" Błaszczykowski is a Polish former professional footballer who played as a winger, currently a businessman and Wisła Kraków's part owner. He started his professional football at Wisła Kraków establishing himself at a young age. In 2007, he joined Borussia Dortmund, where he spent the majority of his career, making over 250 appearances and winning two Bundesliga titles, two DFL-Supercups, and one DFB-Pokal.

Andrzej Zbigniew Biernat is a Polish politician and a member of the Civic Platform party. He served as Minister of Sport and Tourism from November 2013 to June 2015, and he has been a member of the Sejm since September 2005. Prior to his involvement in politics, he worked as teacher in an elementary school and the director of a sports centre in Konstantynów Łódzki.
